open_research_lacunae:
  - what exact app routes currently exist, if any
  - what parser or schema should eventually validate .ion files
  - what proof receipts should be created first from real user movement
  - how John should appear in the interface without becoming an authority figure
  - how to distinguish personal research from canonical product language
  - where any existing test-on-base or mathematical scoring code lives, if it exists outside this seed filesystem
  - what GitHub surfaces and access records should be captured first
  - when and how the remaining .ion bridge files should collapse into .yawn

next_research_move:
  Inspect any existing app, docs repository, GitHub project, or test-on-base
  code when it appears, then wire those surfaces to read from this filesystem
  and write material access records.

